---
title: Pork in Mustard Sauce with roast potatoes and carrots
description: Golden roast potatoes, gently charred carrots and creamy mustard sauce with a kick are combined with tender cooked pork loin for a dish that's classic and comforting in equal measure.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y23_R01_W25_IE_IECP14856-2Main_high-7fdef9b0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipecards/card/64269e376153ff0f6d9ded2b.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipes/pork-in-mustard-sauce-64269e376153ff0f6d9ded2b
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 26.7 g
  saturated fat: 11.6 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 13.8 g
  protein: 40.7 g
  sodium: 3.3 g
  serving size: 686
cuisine: Irish
course: main course
time required: 1 hour
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potato chunks onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25%minutes} to ~{35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Season the @pork loin steak{300%grams} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Trim the @carrots{2} then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large (lined) baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until tender, ~{20%minutes} to ~{25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once the oil is hot, add the pork steaks.

Fry until browned, ~{2%minutes} to ~{3%minutes} on each side.

Reduce the heat to medium and fry for ~{4%minutes} to ~{6%minutes} more, turning every ~{2%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with another plate or #foil{} to rest. IMPORTANT: Pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat.

Drizzle in some @oil{to taste} and fry the garlic for ~{1%minute}.

Add @mustard{2%sachets}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @creme fraiche{125%grams} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{3%minutes} to ~{4%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and add a splash of @water{to taste} if needed.

When everything is cooked, thinly slice the pork widthways and divide between plates.

Serve the potatoes and carrots alongside.

To finish, spoon over the creamy mustard sauce.